Pop singer Chidinma Ekile has been made a brand ambassador of Molped sanitary pad. The singer was unveiled at the official launch of Molped sanitary pad at the Eko Hotel and Suites, Victoria Island, Lagos by Hayat Kimya Nigeria Limited. The company which came to Nigeria in 2015 also produces the popular Molfix diaper brand. The brand ambassador, Chidinma Ekile, who thrilled the audience with songs, including her all-time hit song, Kedike, said it is a brand she is glad to be associated with. “I’ve tried it and I know it is superb,” she said. “So it’s what every young girl needs.” According to the managing director of Hayat Kimya Nigeria, Hakan Misri, Molped comes in two variants. Molped Ultra Soft Sanitary pad which has soft wings, double perforated top-sheet, acquisition layer, absorbent layer and breathable back sheet, while the Maxi Thick Sanitary pad absorbs 3x its weight, has side wings that ensure that it fits perfectly and is nylon-free. And the company’s Marketing Director said the new sanitary pad fulfils desires of the Nigerian woman, addressing especially itchiness, heat, irritation and leakage. 